Speculation:
Battlebond could introduce more partners. The whole concept is two-headed Giant, and lore wise is about a pair of fighters. It would also line up with the “reason” there’s an allied colored focus since there’s only 1 partner for each allied pair
I'd be into that
Unlike the podcast constituents, I don't mind partners
Bruh, I spent the entire time defending the partner mechanic from Dana
I was just enjoying the fireworks
I wasn’t really criticizing the mechanic though. I said I liked it. I was criticizing what the end result is the mechanic winds up being which is Thrassios/x or Tymna/x and a pile of good cards

I think they thought people would take interesting pairs and try to build decks around them but all they do 95% of the time is take the generically strongest card, add a useful color and shuffle in Eternal Witness and Sun Titan

Thrassios is a product of their core Simic design philosophy...value at all cost. Did  they have to make it 4 generic mana? Nope - could've make it 2 generic and Simic. Tymna is an interesting design and interpretation of Orzhov, I think. There's value but it's capped to the number of opponents, and you have to swing at someone.
Yeah but worst case it’s almost always a Pyrexian Arena with upside
You always have to connect
If you’re playing bodies that can’t in edh that’s on you
My point is more that the value has inherent limits. Thrassios is just "generate infinite generic mana, draw your deck"
Sure
